his` is undefined when called.\n\n5. **OrderService.cancelOrder** — the `order.items` is undefined because `OrderRepository.update()` loses fields (Bug 1). After `createOrder` calls `repo.update(id, { status: 'confirmed', total: ... })`, the stored order loses its `items` field.\n\n6. **OrderService.refundOrder** boundary: `daysSinceCreation >= REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS` should be `>` (strictly greater than), because the test expects day 30 to still be allowed.\n\nLet me fix all bugs now."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6129,"cache_read_input_tokens":29707,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6129},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83bd9ab7-df95-494e-8efe-98d5ba10fca2","uuid":"4ea2b8ed-9855-42f2-979c-0d5be463b850"}
